I quite like this SCP - the historical element adds to it, and the effect itself is well described and well thought out.

One nitpick: The essay contains the line:  This indicates that the Foundation only set up containment as of a few years ago, and that it was accessible to civilians as of 2006. It seems hard to believe that that could be the case, without there being public knowledge worldwide of this effect. If that was the intention, that this bridge was publicly accessible as of 2006, this should be expanded upon. Otherwise, that line should be removed.







